main event: A civilian woman reported seeing six round objects darting around the sky over Chicago on February 22, 1952.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be circular and gray in color,The witness reported the objects moved independently without any formation,The estimated altitude of the objects was around 6,000 to 7,000 feet,The objects were approximately 6 to 7 feet in diameter,No sound was reported to be associated with the objects.
sighted object: six round objects in the sky
